caption: Me and a friend stumbled onto Cent' Anni while at Brooklyn Museum in search of nearby Italian cuisine on an early Saturday evening. She was sold because the name means "100 more years" and it just so happened to be her birthday! We decided to get the sautéed calamari and honestly that was the best decision I've made in 2021. The bread that they serve was really good that we ordered another round for our main dish. We ordered the spaghetti limone with capers and the papperdelle bolognese. BOTH dishes were super flavorful, no complaints whatsoever. They have a wonderful selections of wines. Service was fine. For dessert, we opted for the panna cotta which was really good and rich in flavor. Next time, I'm going to go for the tiramisu because...tiramisu.

I have Italian food all the time....My employers are Italian...this food is not it...I actually went based on the reviews, the scent of the calamari, FRESH...my Alfredo grilled chicken handmade tagliatelle pasta was extremely tasteless, UNSEASONED! Diabetic food! Like where’s the seasoning? VERY DISAPPOINTED!!!

Amazing food, drinks, and service! Our server was incredibly attentive, and we never went without a drink. Every dish we ordered was amazing (try the rigatoni) and the frozen hot chocolate was perfect for one of the first spring days we’ve had this year.
Best restaurant in Crown Heights! Eben is amazing!

These ppl can NOT possibly be Italian or know ANYTHING about being Italian!   This is a travesty. I just ordered Rigatoni & the noodles were dry & the meatballs tasted like they were out of a can of Chef Boy Ar Dee.   The sauce was watered down & the Mac & cheese tasted like it came out of a box.  They took a SQUARE piece of Kraft cheese & slapped it on top & it wasn't even melted.  Just look at this HOT mess.  I will NEVER EVER EVER order from here EVER again. If this was the last place to eat on Earth I'd starve n drink water!!!! DO NOT EAT HERE AT ANY COST!!!!! No disrespect to the delivery guy.  He was the BEST thing about placing this order!  If I were able to rate a zero “0” I def would have.  Just looking back at this picture makes me cringe at how bad this food was.

Wildly disappointed by the Black Linguine - total mush and lacking dynamic flavor. I should mention this was a take-out order - and it’s likely had it been plated and not stuffed in a to-go box it would have maintained better form/not turned into one solid pile - so maybe don’t select pasta for take-out. (lesson learned) My bfs dish was also a total disappointment. We ended up tossing both after only a couple bites. The tiramisu was tasty.

This place was extraordinary! I ordered the beet salad as an appetizer, the butternut squash gnocchi as an entree, and a dessert I can’t remember the name of. And let me tell you all of it was amazing from the first bite!! I will be dreaming about that gnocchi for years to come. It melted in my mouth with an explosion of savory flavor. I got the butter and sage sauce. The subtle blends of flavor just wow!! The beet salad with arugula was a nice light treat. I immediately felt renewed from my long day exploring NYC after a few bites. I ordered a sparkling rose which paired well with all the food. I was too full for dessert but still pleasantly ordered it and ate it  late at night in my hotel room. The staff was amazing too. Every one was so friendly, attentive, and considerate. From the host to the bartender to the server and even the other guests. The price wasn’t bad either. It was typical of an upscale place except it had decent portions!! I couldn’t finish it all and my partner and I split and entree too. Definitely check it out for great local cuisine! I could say more but you should find out for yourself!

Fantastic, intimate Italian restaurant with excellent, attentive service. They have a great bartender, who makes delicious cocktails and offer a very reasonable corkage fee if you want to bring your own bottle of wine.  In my opinion, the food is consistently high quality. If you're pressed on time, you can just order an entree (the salmon is my favorite). Or, if you want to stretch things out a bit, you can order a serious four-course Italian meal. They offer great crostini (white bean or liver pate are delish!),   terrific apps (i like the fried calamari) a fresh-made pasta (try the lamb ragu) and a main dish.  As for dessert, they always knock the panna cotta out of the park.  With respect to service, they're fast and attentive. I have a dietary restriction that they're extremely careful about, making sure to ask the kitchen directly when they're not sure. I really appreciate that level of care! When they get slammed, the food can take a few minutes to come out of the kitchen, but in my experience the wait time for food is pretty short.  It's got a lovely atmosphere, too. During the summer, you can sit out in their covered, outdoor backyard. Inside, it's got a cozy, candle lit bistro feel. I love this place and recommend it very highly.

Great food, service and view

I have been to Cent'anni many times over the past three years. Their homemade pastas are amazing, and you can choose your own combination of pasta and sauce. They also have a very affordable brunch menu, with options that include different egg dishes and a drink. Their outdoor seating in the back is lovely during warm weather. I've always had excellent service, and the staff is happy to answer questions about the menu or make recommendations. My favorite, though is the house made gnocchi with the ragu sauce- they even have three different types of gnocchi to choose from! This is one of my favorite spots in Crown Heights, and I will definitely be going back. It is very close to the Franklin Avenue train station, so easy to get to.
Delicious !
Great prices for good food and wine. Service is on point as well. Will definitely be back

Excellent cocktails and delicious pasta. Homemade noodle options are all excellent, and the crostinis are sheer perfection. Half price happy hour cocktails are a great deal for this Crown Heights must-try.
Their Happy Hour is such a great deal, love the cocktails and the rosè brut and they serve handmade pasta. Win. Win. Win.
Great Italian food (the Italian way). Real good fresh pasta.

If you've had fresh pasta before, you know it can be almost a heavenly experience. If you haven't, you need to. Cent'Anni is a great place to enjoy it. Besides the main dishes on the menu, you can customize your choice of pasta, sauce and additions of grilled chicken or shrimp should you choose. The caprese featured fresh tomatoes and basil and Even fresher mozzarella. My main dish-  the special-  was spinach tagliatelle, Alfredo sauce and grilled chicken. Absolutely delicious and not heavy. To finish, the tiramisu was exactly what tiramisu should be and sublime. Service was great including having dishes cleared promptly. Portion size was perfect (side dish of green beans has to be shared.) prices are very reasonable. My first visit here will hopefully be far from my last.
